  "text": "• Semantics-aware rules. Although attribute-based policies allow the specifications of restrictions based on generic attributes or properties of the requestor and the resources, they do not fully exploit the semantic power and reasoning capabilities of emerging web applications. It is therefore important to be able to specify access control rules about subjects accessing the information and about resources to be accessed in terms of rich ontologybased metadata (e.g., Semantic Web-style ones) increasingly available in advanced e-services applications [CITATION_1] .",
